<task id="MCI-017" project="M365 Copilot Integration R1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Adaptive Card Templates — Playbook and Analysis Cards</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <tags>adaptive-cards, m365, ui</tags>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>MCI-010</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create Adaptive Card JSON templates for playbook and analysis presentation in the M365
    Copilot agent. These cards enable users to browse the playbook library, select playbooks
    to run, view risk findings from analysis, and monitor playbook execution progress — all
    within the Copilot chat surface.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior UI developer experienced with Adaptive Cards, M365 Copilot, and JSON templating</role>

  <goal>
    Deliver four production-ready Adaptive Card JSON templates for playbook interactions
    that render correctly in Microsoft 365 Copilot and Teams, following the ASCII mockups
    defined in design.md.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    - Adaptive Card schema version 1.5 (required for M365 Copilot compatibility)
    - All cards must render correctly in both Teams and M365 Copilot surfaces
    - Follow the ASCII mockups from design.md for layout and field placement
    - Include Action.Submit buttons for playbook selection and execution triggers
    - Use data-binding syntax ($\{property}) for dynamic content placeholders
    - Keep card payload under 28 KB (Copilot limit)
    - Support dark mode via Adaptive Card host config (no hard-coded colors)
    - Progress indicator must use ColumnSet-based visual bar (no custom rendering)
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-m365-copilot-integration/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-m365-copilot-integration/spec.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ai/analysis-scopes.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Review the ASCII mockups in design.md for playbook menu, risk findings, playbook library, and progress indicator cards</step>
    <step order="2">Create playbook-menu.json — contextual menu card listing applicable playbooks for the current document/matter with Action.Submit to trigger execution</step>
    <step order="3">Create risk-findings.json — findings card showing risk level badges, finding summaries, severity indicators, and links to detailed analysis</step>
    <step order="4">Create playbook-library.json — browsable catalog card showing available playbooks with descriptions, categories, and selection actions</step>
    <step order="5">Create progress-indicator.json — execution status card with ColumnSet-based progress bar, current step label, and elapsed time</step>
    <step order="6">Validate all four templates against Adaptive Card schema 1.5</step>
    <step order="7">Verify data-binding placeholders match expected playbook API response shapes</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Write</tool>
    <tool>Glob</tool>
    <tool>Grep</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output>src/solutions/CopilotAgent/cards/playbook-menu.json</output>
    <output>src/solutions/CopilotAgent/cards/risk-findings.json</output>
    <output>src/solutions/CopilotAgent/cards/playbook-library.json</output>
    <output>src/solutions/CopilotAgent/cards/progress-indicator.json</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    - All four JSON files are valid Adaptive Card schema 1.5
    - playbook-menu.json lists playbooks with descriptions and Action.Submit buttons for each
    - risk-findings.json displays findings with severity badges (High/Medium/Low) and summary text
    - playbook-library.json presents a browsable catalog with category grouping and selection actions
    - progress-indicator.json shows a visual progress bar using ColumnSet, current step name, and elapsed time
    - All cards use data-binding syntax for dynamic content
    - Action.Submit payloads include playbook ID and execution parameters
    - Card payloads are each under 28 KB
    - No hard-coded colors (dark mode compatible)
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
